#Text=The Golden State Warriors ( 41 - 4 ) defeated the San Antonio Spurs ( 38 - 7 ) 120 - 90 at Oracle Arena on Monday .
#Text=The most anticipated matchup of the season resulted in a surprising 30 - point rout in favor of the Warriors .

#Text=The first of four regular season matchups between the NBA’s two best teams started off shaky for San Antonio , as they converted eight turnovers in the first quarter , and never truly recovered over the next three periods .
#Text=The turnovers started at the expense of Tony Parker , the 15 year veteran who uncharacteristically made bad passes , was out played by Stephen Curry on the defensive end .
#Text=Kawhi Leonard was eventually switched to guard the reigning MVP , but was as unsuccessful as Parker in trying to slow down Curry .
#Text=Leonard led the Spurs in scoring and finished with 16 points on 4 - of - 6 shooting , to go along with five rebounds and two assists .
#Text=David West started in place of Tim Duncan ( knee ) , and also finished in double - figures with 12 points .
#Text=LaMarcus Aldridge was unable to get comfortable in the post , Boris Diaw faced difficulty getting space and Manu Ginobili was equally ineffective from behind the arc and on the drive .
#Text=The loss snapped a 13 game winning streak for San Antonio .
#Text=The Spurs will look to bounce back when they host the Houston Rockets ( 25 - 22 ) on Wednesday .
#Text=The Warriors did not disappoint in their own arena , and were more impressive on the defensive end of the floor as compared to their high powered offense .
#Text=While Golden State dropped 120 points , they harassed the Spurs and forced 26 turnovers which led to an early first half lead , in which they did not let go of the rest of the game .
#Text=The quickness of the Warriors offense caused constant mismatches , especially in the paint after the drive , where Shaun Livingston was the first to wreck havoc in transition .
#Text=Livingston’s 13 points were mostly seen in the second quarter .
#Text=Stephen Curry was far from quiet and started to heat up where Livingston left off , as he scored 37 points on 12 - of - 20 shooting , including six three - pointers in 28 minutes .
#Text=Draymond Green commanded the offense during many of the Warriors possessions , as a result , he rounded out the box score with 11 points , nine rebounds and six assists .
#Text=Six Warriors players finished in double figures with no one player going for more than 28 minutes , as the lead in the fourth quarter was comfortable enough to run the reserves .
#Text=The win marks the fourth straight for Golden State .
#Text=The Warriors will host the Dallas Mavericks ( 25 - 21 ) , one of the only teams to beat them this season , on Wednesday .
